1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>2/10/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>1:46:51 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/manoflaslomas/Dave-1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Starry starry night</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I need to turn a lot of black space into a detailed starry sky in a comic I'm making.  I tried a few filters like noise and grain which worked somewhat but I want yer imput.<br>
<br>
Chances are there are only a coulpe ways of doing it right and a whole bunch of ways of doing it stupid.  I wanna do it right.<br>
<br>
