-Dennis Miller<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#aaaaaa><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upolykarbon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Polykarbon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/pkmini.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Sensei</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>2/10/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>9:52:34 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/profile.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Starry starry night</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">There are a few ways to do it. Back in the old days I used to use frisket paper to mask out my black sky and cover an old toothbrush with opaqe white ink..then flick the bristles at the art by running my thumb down them.<br>
<br>
I use the digital equivelent of that now.<br>
<br>
1)mask out the black area<br>
2)get my airbrush..set it's mode to &quot;Dissolve&quot; and foreground color to white. Opacity about 60%<br>
3)sweep across the pick a few times to get a decent amount of stars (maybe too many even)<br>
4)switch the foreground color to black and sweep some of the area to remove or dim some stars.<br>
5)change the airbrush mode back to normal..opacity 20%, foreground white and give a glow to some of the bigger stars.<br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
1)Fill a black layer with noise<br>
2)Adjust the levels to get the desired dencity of stars<br>
3)create a new black layer above the noise layer<br>
4)with the back and front colors set to black and white..run the &quot;Render Clouds&quot; filter.<br>
5)change the cloud layers blending mode to &quot;Multiply&quot;..that will drop out random patches of stars making it look more natural.</font><P><b><i>See you, Space Cowboy...</i></b><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/umanoflaslomas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>manoflaslomas</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/manoflaslomas/Icon.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Member</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>2/10/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>12:09:34 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/manoflaslomas/Dave-1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Starry starry night</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Thanks man.  I've been reading your tutorials for about a year now but I just started on the BBS and I love it.  Everyone is so nice and helpful.  You've done a great thing here (I mean yer site not just helping me).<br>
